= The Three Fundamental Principles

They are the questions asked in the grave:

1. Knowing your Lord
2. Knowing your Religion
3. Knowing your Prophet, Muḥammad #pbuh

== The First Principle: Knowing Your Lord

=== Main Points

- Our Lord is Allāh, who nurtured us and all creation with His blessings.
- Allāh is the only One worthy of worship, and we worship no one besides Him.
- We come to know our Lord through His signs and His magnificent creation.
- From His signs are the night, the day, the sun, and the moon.
- From His creations are the seven heavens, the seven earths, and all that is
  within and between them.

== The Second Principle: Knowing Your Religion

=== Main Points

- The only religion that Allāh accepts is Islām.
- Islām means: Submission to Allāh through Tawḥīd (monotheism), obedience to
  Him, and disassociating from shirk (polytheism) and its people.

The three Levels of Religion:

1. Islām 
2. Īmān (Faith)
3. Iḥsān (Excellence in Worship)

== The Third Principle: Knowing Your Prophet Muḥammad #pbuh

=== Main Points

1. His Name and Lineage: He is Muḥammad, the son of ‘Abdullāh, the son of ʿAbd
   al-Muṭṭalib, the son of Ḥāshim. Ḥāshim is from the tribe of Quraysh, and
   Quraysh are from the Arabs, who are descendants of Ismāʿīl, the son of
   Ibrāhīm, the Khalīl (friend) of Allāh #salamTHEM.

2. His Age: He lived for sixty-three years:
   - Forty years before prophethood.
   - Twenty-three years as a Prophet and Messenger #pbuh

3. His Prophethood and Message #pbuh:
   - He was given prophethood with the revelation of “*Iqra*'”

   #quran-block[
      ٱقۡرَأۡ بِٱسۡمِ رَبِّكَ ٱلَّذِي خَلَقَ ١
   ][
      Recite in the name of your Lord who created. (Al-ʿAlaq Q96:1)
   ]

   - He was sent as a Messenger with “*Al-Muddathir*”

#quran-block[
   يَٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلۡمُدَّثِّرُ ١ قُمۡ فَأَنذِرۡ ٢
][
   O you who covers himself [with a garment], Arise and warn. (Al-Muddathir Q74:1--2)
]

4. His City and Migration #pbuh:
   - His birthplace: Makkah.
   - His place of migration: Madīnah.

5. The Purpose of His Mission #pbuh:
   - Allāh sent him to warn against Shirk (polytheism)
   - And to call to Tawḥīd (the oneness of Allāh).